  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Boil a <span class=\"text-highlight\">kettle, then</span> peel the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> and cut them <span class=\"text-highlight\">into</span> small bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>red</strong><strong> onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel, top, tail and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> </p>\n<p>Chop the<strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"> chestnut </span>mushrooms </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-2.-2-x200.png",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-2.-2-x400.png",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-2.-2-x700.png",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-2.-2-x1000.png",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-2.-2-x1500.png",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>and <strong>carrot </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> chopped mushrooms </strong>and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>beef mince</strong> and cook for a further 3-4 min until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1451.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
